TY  - JOUR
TI  - Belief-Free Equilibria in Repeated Games
AU  - Ely, Jeffrey C.
AU  - Hörner, Johannes
AU  - Olszewski, Wojciech
AB  - [We introduce a class of strategies that generalizes examples constructed in two-player games under imperfect private monitoring. A sequential equilibrium is belief-free if, after every private history, each player's continuation strategy is optimal independently of his belief about his opponents' private histories. We provide a simple and sharp characterization of equilibrium payoffs using those strategies. While such strategies support a large set of payoffs, they are not rich enough to generate a folk theorem in most games besides the prisoner's dilemma, even when noise vanishes.]
